A. D. Lee, &quot;War in Late Antiquity&quot;
 Publisher: Wiley-Blackwell | ISBN: 0631229264 | edition 2007 | PDF | 309 pages | 2,48 mb

 The first book to focus on the social impact of warfare and the Roman army in Late Antiquity. Explores the implications of war and the army in a broad range of areas encompassing politics, the economy, and social life. Pays particular attention to the experience of war from the perspective ofnon-combatants.Investigates the religious dimension of military life and the role of the army in implementing religious policy.Approaches familiar ubjects from new perspectives, offering novel insights into the many facets of late Roman history.
